---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
import NavBar from "../components/NavBar.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Contact ShipGlowz"
  description="How to reach out about ShipGlowz."
>
  <main class="page-shell">
    <NavBar />

    <section class="section">
      <div class="section-heading">
        <p class="eyebrow">Contact</p>
        <h1 class="page-title">If ShipGlowz matches your pain, the next step is a concrete conversation.</h1>
        <p>
          ShipGlowz is aimed at builders who already feel the cost of lost
          context, weak handoffs, and fragile agent loops. If that is your
          situation, start with the docs, then reach out with the specific
          workflow or shipping problem you want to tighten.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <div class="contact-grid">
        <article class="doc-card">
          <h3>Best way to evaluate fit</h3>
          <p>
            Bring a real workflow problem: repeated context rebuilding, weak
            thread handoffs, drift between docs and implementation, or messy
            server-side delivery operations.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="doc-card">
          <h3>Before reaching out</h3>
          <p>
            Read the docs entry, the workflow doctrine, and the product framing.
            That will make the conversation faster and more precise.
          </p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <div class="cta-panel">
        <p class="eyebrow">Current Entry Points</p>
        <h2>Use the repo and docs as the first contact surface.</h2>
        <p>
          This site is intentionally light. The strongest proof still lives in
          the repository, the decision contracts, and the visible workflow
          mechanics.
        </p>
        <div class="hero-actions">
          <a class="button button-primary" href="https://github.com/dianedef/ShipGlowz">Open GitHub</a>
          <a class="button button-secondary" href="/docs">Read the docs</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>
